# NSSAAF Implementation Methodology

## Golden Rule: Always Start with Roadmap

When implementing any NSSAAF code:

```
1. ALWAYS read: docs/quickref.md (50 lines) ← Start here
2. THEN read: docs/roadmap/README.md (100 lines)
3. THEN read: docs/roadmap/PHASE_*.md (relevant phase)
4. THEN read: docs/design/XX_*.md (relevant design doc)
5. THEN write code
```

## Never Overflow Strategy

### Problem
NSSAAF has 20 design docs (~11,000 lines). Loading all at once overflows context.

### Solution: Progressive Disclosure

**Never load more than 200 lines at once.**

| What you need | Read this | Lines |
|---|---|---|
| Any context | `docs/quickref.md` | 50 |
| Phase overview | `docs/roadmap/PHASE_*.md` | 150 |
| Design detail | `docs/design/02_nssaa_api.md` | 574 |
| Quick lookup | `docs/roadmap/module_index.md` | 50 |

