## Implementation Order

### Phase 1: Foundation (Start Here)

```
1. internal/types/           ← MUST DO FIRST
   - snssai.go: GPSI, SUPI, Snssai validation
   - nssaa_status.go: NssaaStatus enum

2. internal/api/nssaa/
   - handler.go: POST/PUT endpoints
   - request.go, response.go types

3. internal/api/aiw/
   - Same pattern as nssaa/

4. cmd/nssAAF/main.go
   - Wire everything together
```

## Code Template

### API Handler Template

```go
// [Package description]
// Spec: [TS section]
package [module]

// [Type description]
// Source: TS XX.XXX §Y.Z
type [Type] struct {
    // Field documentation
}

// Validate checks if the type is valid.
// Spec: TS XX.XXX §Y.Z
func (t *[Type]) Validate() error {
    // Validation logic
}

// Handler for [operation].
// Spec: TS 29.526 §7.2.X
func (h *Handler) [Method](w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
    // 1. Parse request
    // 2. Validate
    // 3. [Business logic]
    // 4. Return response
}
```

## Validation Checklist (Per Module)

### Types
- [ ] GPSI regex: `^5[0-9]{8,14}$`
- [ ] SUPI regex: `^imu-[0-9]{15}$`
- [ ] Snssai SST: 0-255
- [ ] Snssai SD: 6 hex chars

### API Handlers
- [ ] Request validation before processing
- [ ] Error response: ProblemDetails (RFC 7807)
- [ ] HTTP status: 201, 200, 400, 403, 404, 409, 410, 502, 503, 504
- [ ] Location header on 201
- [ ] X-Request-ID correlation

### Storage
- [ ] GPSI hashed in audit log
- [ ] Session state encrypted
- [ ] Monthly partitions
- [ ] Redis TTL

### Tests
- [ ] Unit test for each public function
- [ ] Validate error cases
- [ ] Mock external dependencies

